issuetype.description: A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.
issuetype.name: Bug

resolution.description: All attempts at reproducing this issue failed, or not enough information was available to reproduce the issue. Reading the code produces no clues as to why this behavior would occur. If more information appears later, please reopen the issue.
resolution.name: Cannot Reproduce

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.
status.name: Resolved

fields.description:
h3. Steps to Reproduce
When I build a project for Android platform, using Titanium SDK 4.0.0 I get the error below. This happens using SDK - RC, Beta3 and Beta2

If I build the exact same project for Android, using Titanium SDK3.5.1GA, it builds fine without error.

comments.body:
Hi ,

We have tested my apps with CLI version 3.4.2, Titanium SDK version 4.0.0.Beta2 and 4.0.0.Beta3 it works fine on android.

Please provide a test case and test environment to reproduce your problem.
That will be really helpful to address your issue.

Thanks
Today I tested on SDK 4.0.0RC and I'm getting the same error.

Hi ,
I tested the issue you reported. It looks like the feature "*Project Compile*" in Appcelerator Studio  is working fine for me. I tested this using the studio build: 4.1.1.201507141126. and SDK 4.1.0 GA 
I recommend you upgrade SDK to the latest build and let us know if you get the error again.
I will mark this ticket as "resolved" since I can't reproduce it. However, feel free to reopen with additional information if you notice otherwise.
Thanks
